<font color="#FF0000">ATTN: VIETNAM VETERANS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec  8 13:24:32 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Dear vets &amp; non-vets:<br><br>
Doug Sibley and others show much courage in forgiving President Clinton for not serving in Vietnam.  This isn't quite analogous, but I am reminded of Lt. Lewis B. Puller, Jr. who lost both legs and part of his hands in Vietnam.  Puller later worked tirelessly for clemency for any vets who deserted.  He even went back to visit with north Vietnamese  soldiers in Vietnam.  &quot;Our stumps are all tangled up, &quot; said Puller after touring a hospital in Hanoi. For him, other soldiers were his brothers, whether they served on the frontlines or not, deserted or not.<br><br>
Peace. 
<p><code>-- mjaffe@mail.sdsu.edu  (Maggie Jaffe) </code><p>


